events.name: New York Knicks at Charlotte Hornets

headlines.description: — Julius Randle scored 33 points, RJ Barrett added 26 and the New York Knicks beat the Charlotte Hornets 121-102 on Friday night for their third straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle stays hot, scores 33 as Knicks top Hornets 121-102

headlines.description: — Buddy Hield scored a season-high 28 points, Tyrese Haliburton had 23 points and 11 assists and the Indiana Pacers beat the Washington Wizards 121-111 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hield, Haliburton lead Pacers past Wizards, 121-111

headlines.description: — Franz Wagner scored 34 points and the Orlando Magic turned to rookie Pablo Banchero in the final minutes Friday night to hold off Toronto 113-109 after the Raptors had wiped out a 20-point deficit in the second half.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wagner, Banchero lead Magic over Raptors 113-109

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant scored 34 points, Kyrie Irving had 33 points and 11 rebounds and the Brooklyn Nets finished a seven-game homestand at 6-1 by beating the Atlanta Hawks 120-116 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant, Irving help Nets edge Hawks to end 6-1 homestand

headlines.description: — Harrison Barnes scored 20 points and Domantas Sabonis had 18 points, 18 rebounds and six assists as the Sacramento Kings rallied for a 106-95 victory over the Cleveland Cavaliers on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barnes scores 20 points, Kings rally to beat Cavs 106-95

headlines.description: — De’Anthony Melton was an LA kid who rooted hard for the Clippers and not that other team in town.
headlines.shortLinkText: 76ers recover in OT after blown lead to beat Lakers 133-122

headlines.description: — Jaren Jackson Jr. had 20 points and four blocks and the Memphis Grizzlies beat the Detroit Pistons 114-103 on Friday night for their fifth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson has 20 points, Grizzlies beat Pistons 114-103

events.name: Phoenix Suns at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson apologized for his 360-degree, one-handed slam dunk that angered the Phoenix Suns at the end of a game that the New Orleans Pelicans were already going to win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Williamson's 35 points lift Pelicans past Suns, 128-117

headlines.description: — D’Angelo Russell scored 20 of his 30 points in the fourth quarter, Rudy Gobert had 22 points and 13 rebounds in his return to Utah and the Minnesota Timberwolves beat the Jazz 118-108 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: D’Angelo Russell powers Timberwolves past Jazz, 118-108

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo fouled out before the Milwaukee Bucks hung on and beat Luka Doncic and the Dallas Mavericks.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lopez layup, Mavs FT woes save Bucks after Giannis fouls out
